Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees.

Peel the @beetroot{2} and chop them into roughly 2cm cubes. Quarter the
@new potatoes{1}. Peel the @red onion{1} and slice in half, roughly chop
each half into 1cm cubes.

On a #baking tray{}, mix the beetroot, potatoes and onions together with
@olive oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a few good grinds of
@pepper{}. Place them on the top shelf of your oven for ~{20-25%minutes}.

> Toss the vegetables after 10 mins to get an even brown colour over the potatoes.

Drain and rinse the @organic lentils{1} and add them to the baking tray
(with the beetroot, potatoes and onions) for the final ~{5%minutes} of
cooking.

Remove the vegetables from your oven. Allow them to cool for ~{5%minutes} in
a #bowl{} before tossing in the @wild rocket{1} and @balsamic cream with figs{1.5}
balsamic dressing and @olive oil{1%tbsp}.

Crumble the @goat's cheese{1} and add to the salad.

Serve in #bowls{}. Scatter over the @walnuts{2} and enjoy!